From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 00:00:00 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: mediatek: make PHY LED pinctrl optional

The AN7581 and MT7988 SoC PHY drivers unconditionally call
devm_pinctrl_get_select(&phydev->mdio.dev, "gbe-led") and log an
error at <3> priority when it fails. This is wrong for two reasons:

1. The LED pinctrl is optional. Boards that drive PHY
   LEDs via GPIO (e.g. Gemtek W1700K) intentionally omit any
   pinctrl-0 reference. In that case devm_pinctrl_get_select()
   returns -ENODEV which is not an error -- it just means "no LED
   pinctrl configured." Logging dev_err here is noisy and
   misleading.

2. Even when a pinctrl-0 IS referenced but fails (e.g. the muxed
   target pin is already claimed by another driver), the failure
   is non-fatal -- the PHY still probes and traffic still flows.
   Only the LED routing is unconfigured. dev_warn is more
   appropriate than dev_err for this case.
---
--- a/drivers/net/phy/mediatek/mtk-ge-soc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/mediatek/mtk-ge-soc.c
@@ -1310,9 +1310,17 @@ static int mt7988_phy_fix_leds_polariti
 
 	/* Only now setup pinctrl to avoid bogus blinking */
 	pinctrl = devm_pinctrl_get_select(&phydev->mdio.dev, "gbe-led");
-	if (IS_ERR(pinctrl))
-		dev_err(&phydev->mdio.bus->dev,
-			"Failed to setup PHY LED pinctrl\n");
+	if (IS_ERR(pinctrl)) {
+		int err = PTR_ERR(pinctrl);
+
+		/* -ENODEV: no pinctrl-0 in DT, LEDs driven by GPIO or not
+		 * used. Stay silent. Other errors are real misconfiguration.
+		 */
+		if (err != -ENODEV)
+			dev_warn(&phydev->mdio.bus->dev,
+				 "Failed to setup PHY LED pinctrl (%pe), LEDs disabled\n",
+				 pinctrl);
+	}
 
 	return 0;
 }
@@ -1415,9 +1423,17 @@ static int an7581_phy_probe(struct phy_
 
 	/* Toggle pinctrl to enable PHY LED */
 	pinctrl = devm_pinctrl_get_select(&phydev->mdio.dev, "gbe-led");
-	if (IS_ERR(pinctrl))
-		dev_err(&phydev->mdio.bus->dev,
-			"Failed to setup PHY LED pinctrl\n");
+	if (IS_ERR(pinctrl)) {
+		int err = PTR_ERR(pinctrl);
+
+		/* -ENODEV: no pinctrl-0 in DT, LEDs driven by GPIO or not
+		 * used. Stay silent. Other errors are real misconfiguration.
+		 */
+		if (err != -ENODEV)
+			dev_warn(&phydev->mdio.bus->dev,
+				 "Failed to setup PHY LED pinctrl (%pe), LEDs disabled\n",
+				 pinctrl);
+	}
 
 	priv = devm_kzalloc(&phydev->mdio.dev, sizeof(*priv), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!priv)
